definition.value: A single species individual organism phenotype affecting the deposition or aggregation of coloring matter in a cell.
A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of coloring matter in a cell is abnormal.
A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of coloring matter in a cell is normal.
A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of coloring matter in a cell is increased.
A single species individual organism phenotype where the accumulation of coloring matter in a cell is decreased.
A single species cell morphology phenotype where hyphal filaments are short in length.
A single species cell morphology phenotype where hyphal filaments are wavy.
A single species phenotype where the dispersal of asexual spores is abnormal (FAO:0000023).
A single species phenotype where the dispersal of asexual spores is normal (FAO:0000023).
A single species phenotype where the dispersal of sexual spores is normal (FAO:0000017).
A single species phenotype where the dispersal of sexual spores is abnormal (FAO:0000017).

A growth phenotype which describes the resistance of individuals or populations after exposure to cypronazole. Typically, organisms are deemed resistant to a chemical if they survive at a concentration of the chemical that does not allow wild type individuals or populations to grow.
A cellular process phenotype in which any process of cellular component organization at the cellular level is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to cyproconazole. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a specified transporter activity is abnormal.
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism is present.
A pathogen host interaction phenotype which affects the pathogen colonization of the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism.
Colonization of host is the action of a pathogen establishing itself in a host. (Covers adhesion, penetration, surface growth).

label.value: pathogen cell to cell migration within host phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype which affects the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism (GO:0044001).

label.value: abnormal pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism is abnormal.

label.value: normal pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism is normal.

label.value: increased pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism is increased compared to normal.

label.value: decreased pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism is decreased compared to normal.

label.value: abolished pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the ability of the pathogen to move directionally within the host organism is abolished (pathogen migration was present within the host and is now absent).

label.value: premature pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism happens sooner than normal.

label.value: delayed pathogen cell to cell migration within host

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction colonization phenotype in which the occurrence of the directional movement of the pathogen within the host organism happens later than normal.

label.value: pathogen host interaction molecular function phenotype

definition.value: A pathogen host interaction phenotype that affects a molecular function such as binding or catalytic activity.

label.value: presence of pathogen growth on host surface

definition.value: A pathogen colonization of host phenotype where the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen on the host surface is present.

label.value: absence of pathogen growth on host surface

definition.value: A pathogen colonization of host phenotype where the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen on the host surface is absent.

label.value: normal formation of pathogen penetration structure prior to entry into host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the formation of the pathogen penetration structure is normal (i.e indistinguishable from wild type).
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism is absent.
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism is decreased.
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism is increased.
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism begins later than normal.
A pathogen entry into host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration into the body, tissues, or cells of the host organism begins sooner than normal.

label.value: absence of pathogen growth within host

definition.value: A pathogen host phenotype in which the vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host is absent.
A pathogen host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host is decreased.

label.value: delayed timing of pathogen growth within host

definition.value: A pathogen host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host begins later than normal.
A pathogen host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host begins sooner than normal.
A pathogen host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of vegetative growth or proliferation of the pathogen inside the host is increased.

label.value: abnormal formation of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the formation of the pathogen penetration structure is abnormal (i.e different than wild-type).

label.value: decreased number of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration stuctures near the host are decreased.

label.value: decreased size of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the size of pathogen penetration stuctures near the host are decreased.

label.value: increased number of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the frequency of occurrence of pathogen penetration stuctures near the host are increased.

label.value: increased size of pathogen penetration structure when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the size of pathogen penetration stuctures near the host are increased.

label.value: delayed timing of pathogen penetration structure formation when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the formation of pathogen specialized penetration structure begins later than normal.

label.value: premature pathogen penetration structure formation when near host

definition.value: A pathogen growth with host phenotype in which the formation of pathogen specialized penetration structure begins sooner than normal.

A growth phenotype which describes the resistance of individuals or populations after exposure to carboxin. Typically, organisms are deemed resistant to a chemical if they survive at a concentration of the chemical that does not allow wild type individuals or populations to grow.

A growth phenotype which describes the sensitivity of individuals or populations after exposure to carboxin. Typically, organisms are deemed sensitive to a chemical if they stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of the chemical that allows wild type individuals or populations to grow.

A cellular process phenotype in which cell wall organization is abnormal. Cell wall organization results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the fungal-type cell wall.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a specified transporter activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
